  "title": "LinkedIn post",
  "description": "Priority: High\n\nDue: Friday (June 12)\n\nContent:\n\nWe don't just tell clients how to use AI. We run our own company on it.\n\nThis month we made our entire organization queryable through AI: our data warehouse, financials, CRM, time tracking, meeting notes, and codebase, all connected in one place.\n\nA few things that now run on autopilot:\n\n- A weekly business overview with pipeline movement, project status, and spend, compiled for us.\n- A daily briefing that researches our upcoming calls, preps the docs, and drafts context-aware follow-up emails for contacts due in the CRM.\n- Automated CRM updates and follow-up drafts after every client call.\n- Month-end financials and reporting, plus analytics on demand.\n\nThe point isn't the tooling. It's that we'd never recommend a workflow we haven't put our own operation through first.\n\nIf you're trying to figure out how AI can help your business, that's a conversation we love having. Book a free discovery call. Link in the comments.\n",
